<br>
Self-only buffs sound like a great idea.  Faervas and I think that melees should be limited to stock armor (heh, summoned mage leather would be even better) and the rusty/fine steel weapon of their choice to make sure that the fight was won on skill, not items.  Casters would have to be in similarly sucky garb (nothing with Flowing Thought on it, please), and resist gear is right out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  But it seems to me that the individual participants should be able to work out whatever 'ground rules' they chose, as long as it didn't take them an act of Congress to get their equipment lists approved (hence the universally weak equipment suggestion).<br>
<br>
I *love* the idea; pick a time and place for the meetings and firm things up and we are there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  It's been a long time since we left our (PvP) text Mud, and I am afraid we've gotten a bit rusty...<br>
